general commands

links to follow up
// for tracking
https://www.git-tower.com/learn/git/faq/track-remote-upstream-branch


*git init

*git add . // git add *

*git status

*git commit -m"<message>"

*git push origin <branch-name>

*git pull origin <branch-name>

*git remote add origin <repository-url>

*git log

*git log --oneline

=> create a new branch 
*git branch <name-of-branch>

=>see all the branchs and origins
*git branch -a

=>show the changes on the branch || HEAD
*git branch -v

=>remove all the changes since last commit
*git reset --hard

=>new local branch tracking a remote branch
*git switch <branch-name>
*git switch -c <branch> --track <remote>/<branch-name>
or
git checkout --track origin/dev

=>pushing a detached head to origin branch
*git push HEAD:<branch-name>

